cal hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Joan was born in 1204. She married Henry le Fleming I in 1219, in Pulborough, Sussex, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 3 sons."},"et":{"1204–":"1204–Surnud","1200–Male":"1200–Surnud","1218–1263":"1218–1263","1220–1263":"1220–1263","–Male":"Surnud","1204–Female":"1204–Surnud","1204":"1204","1200":"1200","1220":"1220","1263":"1263","ABT 1218":"umbes 1218","1219":"1219","1218":"1218","Sapperton, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Sapperton, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Pulborough, Sussexshire, England":"Pulborough, Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sapperton, Gloucester, England":"Sapperton, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1204–":"1204–Kuollut","1200–Male":"1200–Kuollut","1218–1263":"1218–1263","1220–1263":"1220–1263","–Male":"Kuollut","1204–Female":"1204–Kuollut","1204":"1204","1200":"1200","1220":"1220","1263":"1263","ABT 1218":"noin 1218","1219":"1219","1218":"1218","Sapperton, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Sapperton, Gloucestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Pulborough, Sussexshire, England":"Pulborough, Sussex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Sapperton, Gloucester, England":"Sapperton, Gloucestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1204–":"1204–Décédée","1200–Male":"1200–Décédé","1218–1263":"1218–1263","1220–1263":"1220–1263","–Male":"Décédé","1204–Female":"1204–Décédée","1204":"1204","1200":"1200","1220":"1220","1263":"